WEBVTT

00:03.102 --> 00:05.336
¶ Boy, the way
Glenn Miller played ¶

00:05.404 --> 00:08.840
¶ songs that made
the hit parade ¶

00:08.908 --> 00:12.644
¶ guys like us
we had it made ¶

00:12.712 --> 00:15.780
[ together ]
¶ those were the days ¶

00:15.848 --> 00:19.183
<i>¶ and you knew</i>
<i> </i> <i> where you were then ¶</i>

00:19.251 --> 00:23.221
[ Archie ]
¶ girls were girls
and men were men ¶

00:23.288 --> 00:25.724
[ Archie, Edith ]
¶ mister, we could use a man ¶

00:25.791 --> 00:29.560
¶ like Herbert hoover again ¶

00:29.628 --> 00:32.931
[ Archie ]
¶ didn't need no welfare state ¶

00:32.999 --> 00:36.200
[ Edith ]
¶ everybody pulled his weight ¶

00:36.268 --> 00:40.138
[ Archie, Edith ]
¶ gee, our old lasalle
ran great ¶

00:40.205 --> 00:44.643
¶ those were the days ¶

00:51.917 --> 00:54.119
okay, what do
ya got, Gloria?

00:54.186 --> 00:56.220
A pair of kings.

00:56.288 --> 00:59.223
Small straight
to the seven.
What do ya got, ma?

00:59.291 --> 01:02.193
Well, it's not very good.

01:02.261 --> 01:05.030
It was real good
when I started out.

01:05.096 --> 01:07.298
See, nine, nine, nine.

01:07.366 --> 01:11.903
But the two you gave me
spoiled it all-- two queens.

01:11.971 --> 01:14.839
It's a full house.
You won the game.
You won.

01:14.907 --> 01:17.776
Really? Oh, my. Oh.

01:17.843 --> 01:22.380
I better look at the stew.
Your father will be here
any minute.

01:22.447 --> 01:26.885
We each owe a dime to the pot.
Okay, that's 10--
20 cents more.

01:26.952 --> 01:31.056
Ma, we got it!
That's makes a total
of $30 in the family pot.

01:31.123 --> 01:35.160
- That means you can do it.
- Do? Do what?

01:35.227 --> 01:37.796
Don't you remember
that mom wrote a song
a couple months ago?

01:37.863 --> 01:40.065
- A song?
- You remember.

01:40.132 --> 01:42.867
¶ Everyone is someone
if you love them ¶

01:42.935 --> 01:45.670
yeah, I remember.

01:45.738 --> 01:49.540
Why don't you read him
that letter you got from the
wish upon a star song company.

01:49.608 --> 01:51.876
Oh, yeah, here it is.

01:53.145 --> 01:55.346
"Dear Mrs. bunker--

01:55.414 --> 01:59.283
"your poem, or as we say
in the business,

01:59.351 --> 02:03.287
"your lyric--
[ Chuckles ]

02:03.355 --> 02:07.192
"Has been accepted
by our panel of experts.

02:07.259 --> 02:12.263
"As soon as we receive
your check for $30
handling fee,

02:12.331 --> 02:14.332
"your poem will be set
to music...

02:14.399 --> 02:18.737
"By one of the many
top composers on our staff...

02:18.804 --> 02:22.340
And on its way
to super stardom."

02:22.407 --> 02:26.044
- Isn't it terrific?
- Edith!

02:26.112 --> 02:29.013
Gloria, get the stew on.

02:29.081 --> 02:32.316
Oh, hello, Archie.

02:33.385 --> 02:35.319
How are you?
Hello. Hello.

02:35.387 --> 02:37.321
How was your day?

02:37.389 --> 02:39.590
It was a laugh riot.

02:40.726 --> 02:42.660
One jolly moment
after the other.

02:42.728 --> 02:46.197
That's why you see me
standing here like
the bluebird of happiness.

02:46.265 --> 02:50.101
What's the matter, arch?
I've never seen you
so upset.

02:50.169 --> 02:52.503
Oh, you never read
the papers, huh?

02:52.571 --> 02:54.672
Don't you know
what's goin' on?

02:54.740 --> 02:58.910
In here it says 19 robberies
reported in queens district.

02:58.978 --> 03:00.912
Two of them right
around here.

03:00.980 --> 03:03.848
Yesterday Ryan's gas station
a couple of blocks away.

03:03.916 --> 03:07.952
And today I'm passing old lady
crimski's bakery on the way
to the subway this morning.

03:08.020 --> 03:11.156
What do you think I saw?
What they didn't do to her.

03:11.223 --> 03:15.994
First of all
they robbed 180 bucks
right out of her stocking.

03:16.061 --> 03:18.263
Then just for spite,
they ruin the joint.

03:18.330 --> 03:20.932
Cheesecake splashed
all over the walls.

03:21.000 --> 03:23.301
Bagels rolling out
to the sidewalk.

03:23.368 --> 03:26.671
I'm telling you,
we're livin' in a jungle,
that's what-- a jungle.

03:26.738 --> 03:29.307
- But you know what I got?
- Malaria.

03:36.548 --> 03:38.883
Funny, funny, funny.

03:38.951 --> 03:43.188
The whole world is fallin'
apart and the meathead here
is makin' jokes.

03:43.255 --> 03:47.025
Well, I'm takin' some action
beginning with this little
surprise right here.

03:47.092 --> 03:51.329
You got a surprise, Archie?
We got a surprise too.

03:51.396 --> 03:53.431
Save it, will ya.

03:53.498 --> 03:57.735
Why don't you tell us
your surprise first?

03:57.803 --> 04:01.505
I think I will, Edith.

04:01.573 --> 04:06.110
See this here?
It looks like a regular little
tape recorder, don't it?

04:06.178 --> 04:09.747
- But you know what that is?
- A save your home alarm system.

04:09.815 --> 04:12.350
How'd you know that?

04:12.417 --> 04:14.919
It says it right there
on the label--
save your home alarm system.

04:17.589 --> 04:21.425
Well, labels
don't tell you nothin'.
I'll tell you what this is.

04:21.493 --> 04:24.095
This is a save your home
alarm system.

04:27.099 --> 04:29.868
Now, you hook this up
all over.

04:29.935 --> 04:33.905
And if any burglar tries
to get in any door
or a window,

04:33.973 --> 04:36.074
wait till you hear
what happens.

04:36.141 --> 04:38.176
[ Dog barking
ferociously on tape ]

04:42.714 --> 04:45.649
What are you laughin' at?
This is a serious thing here.

04:45.717 --> 04:48.086
[ Barking continues ]

04:50.122 --> 04:53.424
Huh? Ah, what do you
think of that?

04:53.492 --> 04:57.929
Sounds like
a sweet old dog to me.

04:59.265 --> 05:01.766
What are you
talkin' about, Edith?

05:03.502 --> 05:05.436
This thing is proved.

05:05.504 --> 05:08.672
This thing gives you
all the protection
of a real killer dog.

05:08.740 --> 05:10.674
Now, come on.
Let's eat, huh?

05:10.742 --> 05:13.244
Well, dinner's ready.
Come on, everybody.

05:13.312 --> 05:15.646
Archie, how much did you
pay for that thing?

05:15.714 --> 05:19.918
Five dollars down
to begin, and $5 a week
to a total of 40 bucks.

05:19.985 --> 05:22.486
It's the cheapest home
insurance anywheres around.

05:22.554 --> 05:25.957
Forty bucks?
Gee, it sounds like
law and order's big business.

05:26.025 --> 05:28.026
Pass the salt, please?

05:28.093 --> 05:30.261
Daddy, can mom tell you
about her surprise now?

05:30.329 --> 05:33.097
Certainly. It's a free
country, ain't it?

05:33.165 --> 05:34.799
Oh, I don't--

05:34.866 --> 05:37.302
go on. Tell him, ma.

05:37.369 --> 05:39.304
Well, Archie,

05:39.371 --> 05:43.041
Gloria and me saw this ad
in a movie magazine.

05:43.108 --> 05:46.411
It said,
"wanted, your poems.

05:46.478 --> 05:50.348
Top composers
will set to music."

05:50.416 --> 05:54.986
So I wrote a poem
and we sent it in.
And guess what.

05:55.054 --> 05:57.755
They loved it.
Pass the salt.

05:57.823 --> 06:00.024
He wasn't a bit surprised.

06:00.092 --> 06:05.396
Why should I be surprised,
Edith? I always knew you
was a great "poetress,"

06:05.464 --> 06:09.200
ever since that time
I was sick and you sent me
the get-well card.

06:09.268 --> 06:12.603
I'll never forget it.
"Get well quickly.
Oh, please do.

06:12.671 --> 06:15.406
'Cause I'm cryin',
boo-hoo-hoo."

06:19.011 --> 06:22.847
So why should I be surprised
that them crooks
loved your poem?

06:22.914 --> 06:27.318
Don't call 'em crooks, daddy.
They loved mom's poem
and they wanna set it to music.

06:27.386 --> 06:30.455
Oh, sure. How much they
wanna hit you up for, Edith?

06:30.522 --> 06:33.591
Only $30 for handling fees.

06:33.658 --> 06:37.328
Oh, please, Edith,
don't you see?
This thing is a con.

06:37.396 --> 06:41.932
These guys open an office in a
different state every month to
keep one jump ahead of the cops.

06:42.001 --> 06:44.802
Some of them go around
in mobile homes.

06:44.870 --> 06:47.805
Besides, where you
gonna get the 30 bucks
to begin with?

06:47.873 --> 06:50.908
The family pot.
As of today,
there's $30 in it.

06:50.976 --> 06:54.445
Oh, the family pot.
Listen, the answer
to that is no.

06:54.513 --> 06:57.248
Now that's for special
occasions, for emergencies.

06:57.316 --> 07:00.885
I ain't gonna let no
shyster music company get
their hand into my pot.

07:00.952 --> 07:03.988
Our pot, daddy.
<i>Same thing,</i>
<i> </i> <i>same thing.</i>

07:04.056 --> 07:05.990
Archie.
Archie, wait a second.

07:07.426 --> 07:11.462
Can I talk to you?
Man to man.

07:18.170 --> 07:21.205
I once had a date
with this girl named Arlene.

07:21.273 --> 07:25.443
Yeah? I once shared
an ice cream with
a midget. So what?

07:26.912 --> 07:28.846
Archie, I'm serious.

07:28.914 --> 07:32.550
This girl Arlene had me over
for dinner and she cooked me
this leg of lamb.

07:32.617 --> 07:37.321
Now, I can't stand leg of lamb,
but it was important to this
girl that I like her cooking.

07:37.389 --> 07:41.225
So I forced it down.
It was a small thing,
but it made her happy.

07:41.293 --> 07:43.227
You see what
I'm trying to say?

07:43.295 --> 07:46.997
You want me to tell Edith
not to serve leg of lamb.
That ain't it?

07:47.066 --> 07:50.535
No!
Well, what the hell
is it then?

07:50.602 --> 07:55.540
Archie, there are times
in your life when you shouldn't
rain on someone else's parade.

07:55.607 --> 07:59.743
Geez, you sound
like a regular
Billy sol Graham there.

07:59.811 --> 08:01.679
Archie--

08:04.316 --> 08:06.850
the money from the family pot
should be used--

08:06.918 --> 08:09.753
cut it.
Don't try to soft-soap me.

08:09.821 --> 08:12.723
Now, you ain't talkin' me
into lettin' them blow
the family pot...

08:12.791 --> 08:15.059
For no phony music company.
Archie.

08:15.127 --> 08:18.196
Just a minute.
Come here. I wanna
show you something.

08:18.263 --> 08:21.932
What is it?
I didn't say nothin' about this
when the women was here.

08:22.000 --> 08:25.236
I didn't want them
getting excited
about anything.

08:25.304 --> 08:28.573
Now take a look at this.

08:28.640 --> 08:32.143
A gun!
Shh! Shut up!
Will you keep quiet.

08:32.211 --> 08:34.278
I don't want them to hear!

08:34.346 --> 08:37.715
This ain't just a gun.
This is a luger.

08:37.782 --> 08:40.683
World war ii. That's
a terrific German weapon.

08:40.751 --> 08:43.321
Willie mears is gonna
sell me this for 20 bucks.

08:43.388 --> 08:45.756
Between this and the dog
we'll be protected.

08:45.824 --> 08:47.758
You're gonna buy a gun?
Shh!

08:47.826 --> 08:50.628
Archie, I can understand
that dumb taped dog.
It can't hurt anybody.

08:50.695 --> 08:52.930
But a gun!
Will you dummy up, huh!

08:52.998 --> 08:55.933
I don't want them
to get all upset in there.
Ma!

08:56.001 --> 08:59.604
What are you doin'?
What are you doin'?
Gloria, come in here.

08:59.671 --> 09:02.607
- What is it?
- Go on back out to the kitchen.
It's nothin'.

09:02.674 --> 09:06.076
Archie wants
to buy a gun.
What a fink!

09:06.145 --> 09:08.078
That's right.
That's right.

09:08.147 --> 09:10.748
A gun?
Oh, my goodness!
A gun? Where?

09:10.815 --> 09:13.384
Right over here.
Get out of
my pocket there!

09:13.452 --> 09:17.488
That's the reason he doesn't
wanna give you the money.
He wants it to buy a gun.

09:17.556 --> 09:19.490
- Archie!
- Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

09:19.558 --> 09:21.992
What is wrong with that?

09:22.060 --> 09:26.397
I am interested in
the protection of my home--
the defense of my family.

09:26.465 --> 09:29.167
Oh! Oh, that's
terrific. Yeah.

09:29.234 --> 09:32.736
You're gonna buy
a taped dog and a gun.
That's $60 for defense...

09:32.804 --> 09:35.439
Against only $30
for the song.
[ Archie ] Right.

09:35.507 --> 09:39.677
Archie, when it's a question
of the destructive man
versus the creative man,

09:39.744 --> 09:42.146
the creative man always
gets the shaft.

09:42.214 --> 09:46.450
The shaft? Is that anything
like the Oscar?

09:48.720 --> 09:52.256
Daddy, are you really
gonna buy a gun?

09:52.324 --> 09:54.625
I'm doin' it for youse.

09:54.693 --> 09:58.362
[ All chattering at once ]

09:58.430 --> 10:01.999
Wait a minute, everybody.
Quiet down 'cause I'm gonna
tell you something.

10:02.067 --> 10:04.068
The discussion is over.

10:05.604 --> 10:09.373
No! Not according
to the rules of
the family pot.

10:09.441 --> 10:12.142
The use of the family pot
shall be determined
in a Democratic way...

10:12.211 --> 10:15.913
By a majority vote
of the members of this family
and assigned by all of us.

10:15.980 --> 10:18.949
I don't care what that says.
I'm gonna buy that gun.

10:19.017 --> 10:22.720
When it comes to defense,
democracy's gonna have to wait.

10:22.787 --> 10:25.122
You're impossible, daddy.

10:25.190 --> 10:27.692
But you signed the rules too,
and they say we should vote.

10:27.759 --> 10:30.961
All right, go ahead then
and vote away your property.

10:31.029 --> 10:35.299
Vote away your homes,
your valuables,
perhaps your very lives.

10:35.367 --> 10:39.903
All those in favor of using
the money from the family pot
for the song, say aye.

10:39.971 --> 10:42.540
Aye.
All those opposed,
say nay.

10:42.608 --> 10:45.976
- I ain't gonna vote.
- Then the ayes have it.

10:46.044 --> 10:49.614
The money goes for the song.
That's right. And you gotta
give back the gun.

10:49.681 --> 10:52.250
Come on, now. Come on.
Get away from me!

10:52.317 --> 10:54.685
It makes me so happy.
Get away from me,
all of youse.

10:54.753 --> 10:58.289
Come on, daddy.
You won't regret it when
the song becomes a big hit.

10:58.357 --> 11:00.824
Oh, yeah, sure.
Let me tell you somethin'.

11:00.892 --> 11:03.060
When the first burglar
breaks into this house...

11:03.128 --> 11:07.498
And youse all turn to me
and holler, "do something!"
You know what I'm gonna do?

11:07.566 --> 11:11.535
I'm gonna turn right around back
and say, "sing, Edith."

11:16.875 --> 11:19.810
[ Windowsill creaking ]

11:21.813 --> 11:24.515
[ Taped dog barking ]

11:29.454 --> 11:31.555
Here, doggy.

11:31.623 --> 11:34.558
<i>[ Barking continues ]</i>

11:37.362 --> 11:39.297
Here, doggy.

11:41.333 --> 11:45.903
Where you at, doggy?
Here, poochy.
[ Whistles ]

11:45.970 --> 11:48.872
Here, little pooch.
Come on to papa, doggy.

11:48.940 --> 11:50.874
Here, little pooch.

11:54.946 --> 11:57.181
Here he is, Horace.

11:58.216 --> 12:00.150
[ Barking stops ]

12:01.620 --> 12:04.822
Bye-bye, doggy.

12:04.889 --> 12:07.157
Another electric dog, man.

12:07.225 --> 12:11.495
Somebody must be makin'
a whole lot of money off these
white folks with these things.

12:11.563 --> 12:14.231
Be funny if the cat
was black.

12:18.503 --> 12:20.971
The fuzz is still
buzzing, man.

12:21.039 --> 12:23.474
We're gonna have to hang out
here for a little while.

12:27.278 --> 12:30.614
Whoo! Would you look
at this dump?

12:33.618 --> 12:36.654
Yeah, man, how can
they live like this?

12:39.358 --> 12:42.693
The paint's peelin',
the furniture's fallin'
all apart,

12:42.761 --> 12:46.831
but they all got
that fancy color tv sittin'
right in the middle of it.

12:48.032 --> 12:50.534
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

12:50.602 --> 12:53.270
Well, man, you know they've
got to have somethin'...

12:53.338 --> 12:56.841
To keep their mind
off of their misery.

12:56.908 --> 13:00.378
You know, everybody can't be
as affluent as we is.

13:04.883 --> 13:07.084
[ Sniffs ]
What's the matter?

13:07.151 --> 13:09.420
Ain't that somethin'?
<i>What?</i>

13:09.488 --> 13:11.422
Take a sniff.

13:11.490 --> 13:14.191
[ Sniffs ]
Yeah?

13:14.259 --> 13:18.128
White people's homes
all got that funny smell.

13:20.499 --> 13:23.200
[ Ringing ]

13:24.669 --> 13:26.737
You wasn't expectin'
no call, was you?

13:28.139 --> 13:31.241
No, man. I didn't even know
I had a phone.

13:31.309 --> 13:34.712
Lookit here. You check out
the kitchen and I'll check out
the phone, all right?

13:36.214 --> 13:40.183
Hello? Who?
Mr. bunker?

13:40.251 --> 13:44.121
Oh, I'm sorry.
Mr. bunker's indisposed
at the moment.

13:44.188 --> 13:47.525
Oh, this is
the family physician.

13:47.592 --> 13:49.527
Dr. black.

13:51.930 --> 13:55.098
Oh, nothing serious.
He'll be just fine.

13:55.166 --> 13:59.102
Uh-huh. What was that? Oh.

13:59.170 --> 14:02.272
Mrs. bunker,
did you hear that?

14:02.340 --> 14:07.678
Your neighbor Mr. mcnab
just called and said that
two fellas just robbed--

14:07.746 --> 14:10.481
what was that, Mr. mcnab?

14:10.549 --> 14:13.283
Oh. Two jigaboos...

14:17.121 --> 14:19.623
Just robbed Morgan's
jewelry store...

14:19.691 --> 14:22.827
And they're hiding somewhere
in the neighborhood.

14:22.894 --> 14:25.763
Yes, I'll tell him.
Good-bye.

14:27.298 --> 14:29.967
<i>Hey, what you got</i>
<i>there, man?</i>
<i>Electric appliances.</i>

14:30.034 --> 14:32.970
Man, what these white folks
won't waste their money on.

14:34.573 --> 14:37.040
<i>[ Man chattering ]</i>
<i>Let's go out</i>
<i>the back door.</i>

14:37.108 --> 14:40.177
No, no, cops.
Up the stairs. Come on.

14:40.244 --> 14:42.646
<i>[ Archie ]</i>
<i>Hold it, Edith.</i>
<i>Don't open the door.</i>

14:42.714 --> 14:45.916
<i>[ Edith ] Why not?</i>
<i>First I gotta turn off</i>
<i>the dog alarm.</i>

14:45.984 --> 14:48.318
<i>Oh.</i>
<i>Go ahead.</i>

14:50.254 --> 14:53.891
I wanna tell you something.
That was one of the funniest
moving pictures I ever seen.

14:53.959 --> 14:57.528
I can't believe it.
He finally liked a movie
we recommended.

14:57.596 --> 14:59.530
Well, certainly I liked it.

14:59.598 --> 15:03.801
It wasn't one of them nowaday
ones with everybody jumpin' into
bed three and four at a clip.

15:08.907 --> 15:11.909
This wasn't a dirty picture.
It was a funny picture.

15:11.977 --> 15:15.646
Buster keaton, one of
the funniest guys ever.
I nearly--

15:15.714 --> 15:20.183
you remember when he took
the brass spittoon, he put it
down over that guy's head?

15:20.251 --> 15:23.220
Now that's funny enough,
but when he reaches for
that ball bat...

15:23.287 --> 15:27.124
And goes bongo, bongo, bongo,
I thought I wet my drawers.

